The Collect 


O LORD Christ, as Thou didst at this season rise 
from death into the wondrous power of an endless 
life, so may we by Thy most gracious help rise from 
the darkness of sin into the ineffabie splendour of 
conscious life in Thee, O Light of Light, Who livest 
and reignest for evermore. R. Amen. 


The Epistle 


The Epistle is taken from the second and third chap- 
ters of the Epistle of St. Paul the Apostle to the Colos- 
sians, beginning at the sixth verse. 


AS ye have therefore received Christ Jesus the 
Lord, so walk ye in Him; rooted and built up in 
Him, and stablished in the faith, as ye have been 
taught, abounding therein with thanksgiving. For 
in Him dwelleth all the fullness of the Godhead bod- 
ily; and ye are complete in Him, Who is the Head 
of all principality and power; buried with Him in 
baptism, wherein also ye are risen with Him through 
the faith of the operation of God, Who hath raised 
Him from the dead. If ye then be risen with Christ, 
seek those things which are above, where Christ 


