ye, except ye abide in Me. He that abideth in Me, 
and I in him, the same bringeth forth much fruit; 
for without Me ye can do nothing. Herein is My 
Father glorified, that ye bear much fruit; so shall 
ye be My disciples. As the Father hath loved Me, 
so have I loved you; continue ye in My love. If ye 
keep My commandments, ye shall abide in My love; 
even as I have kept My Father’s commandments, 
and abide in His love. These things have I spoken 
unto you, that My joy might remain in you, and 
that your joy might be full. These things I com- 
mand you, that ye love one another. 





