For the flesh lusteth against the Spirit, and the Spir- 
lit against the flesh; and these are contrary the one 
ito the other, so that ye cannot do the things that ye 
\would. The fruit of the spirit is love, joy, peace, long- 
suffering, gentleness, goodness, faith, meekness, temper- 
lance; against such there is no law. If we live in the 
‘Spirit, let us also walk in the Spirit. 


