I SAY unto you which hear: Love your enemies, 
do good to them which hate you, bless them that curse 
you, and pray for them which despitefully use you. 
And as ye would that men should do to you, do ye 
also to them likewise. Love ye your enemies, and do 
‘good and lend, hoping for nothing again; and your 
reward shall be great, and ye shall be the children 
of the Highest, for He is kind unto the unthankful 
and to the evil. Be ye therefore merciful, as your 
