from Galilee to Jordan unto John, to be baptized 
of Him. But John forbad Him, saying: I have 
need to be baptized of Thee, and comest Thou to 
me? And Jesus said unto him: Suffer it to be so 
now; for thus it becometh us to fulfil all righteous- 
ness. Then he suffered Him. And Jesus, when He 
was baptized, went up straightway out of the water; 
and, lo, the heavens were opened unto Him, and He 


